<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN374">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kāṉaṉ mēyntu viyaṉpulat talkum</l>
<l>pulvā yiralai neṟṟi yaṉṉa</l>
<l>polamilaṅku ceṉṉiya pāṟumayir viyarppat</l>
<l>taṇpaṉi yuṟaikkum pularā ñāṅkar</l>
<l>maṉṟap palaviṉ mālvarai poruntiyeṉ</l>
<l>ṟeṇkaṇ mākkiṇai teḷirppa voṟṟi</l>
<l>yiruṅkalai yōrppa vicaiik kāṇvarak</l>
<l>karuṅkōṟ kuṟiñci yaṭukkam pāṭap</l>
<l>pulippaṟ ṟālip puṉṟalaic ciṟāar</l>
<l>māṉkaṇ makaḷirk kāṉṟē rakaṉṟuvā</l>
<l>cilaippāṟ paṭṭa muḷavumāṉ koḻuṅkuṟai</l>
<l>viṭarmukai yaṭukkattuc ciṉaimutir cāntap</l>
<l>pukarmuka vēḻattu maruppoṭu mūṉṟu</l>
<l>miruṅkēḻ vayappuli variyataṭ kuvaii</l>
<l>viruntiṟai nalku nāṭa ṉeṅkōṉ</l>
<l>kaḻaṟoṭi yāa yaṇṭiraṉ pōla</l>
<l>vaṇmaiyu muṭaiyaiyō ñāyiṟu</l>
<l>koṉviḷaṅ kutiyāl vicumpi ṉāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>As, (8d)</l>
<l>so that the dishevelled hair one [my] golden shining head perspires (3)</l>
<l>like the forehead of the Iralai deer (2)</l>
<l>that grazes in the seashore grove [and] stays in the wide fields, (1)</l>
<l>at the time that does not become dry when cool dew drips, (4)</l>
<l>I join the big mountain with a jackfruit tree in a village common, (5)</l>
<l>beat my clear-eyed Kiṇai drum so that it sounds, (6)</l>
<l>sounding [it] while a dark stag/monkey listens, [and] visibly (7)</l>
<l>sing by the slope with black-stalked Kuṟiñci, (8)</l>
<l>resembling Āay Aṇṭiraṉ with anklets [and] bracelets, (16),</l>
<l>our king, man from a land, where grants a seat at [his] feast/to guests (15)</l>
<l>[even] the young man, after having departed to search the forest, with doe-eyed women (10)</l>
<l>[and] ruddy-haired children with tiger-tooth Tālis, (9)</l>
<l>[and] heaped on the striped skin of a dark, lustrous, strong tiger (14)</l>
<l>three things, [namely] with the tusk of an elephant bull with spotted face (13)</l>
<l>mature sandal from the branches in the mountain side with clefts [and] caves, (12)</l>
<l>[and] fat pieces of a male porcupine that fell to the bow, (11)</l>
<l>– do you also possess munificence, sun? (17)</l>
<l>You would vainly shine in the sky. (18)</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="9-16">
<l>resembling Āay Aṇṭiraṉ with anklets [and] bracelets, (16),</l>
<l>our king, man from a land, who grants a seat at [his] feast/to guests (15)</l>
<l>after heaping on the striped skin of a dark, lustrous, strong tiger (14)</l>
<l>three things, [namely] with the tusk of an elephant bull with spotted face (13)</l>
<l>mature sandal from the branches in the mountain side with clefts [and] caves, (12)</l>
<l>[and] fat pieces of a male porcupine that fell to the bow, (11)</l>
<l>when ruddy-haired youngsters with tiger-tooth Tālis (9)</l>
<l>had departed to search the forest for the sake of doe-eyed women [and] come back, (10)   </l>
</lg>
</lg>
